The Human Rights Commission is investigating claims that medical aid schemes are discriminating against black medical professionals. eNCA’s Janke Tolmay has more. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Human Rights Commission is investigating claims that medical aid schemes are discriminating against black medical professionals. The National Health Care Professionals Association says its Black, Indian and Coloured members are being bullied and racially profiled. READ: Medical aids accused of racist mistreatment The SAHRC heard from various medical aid schemes regarding allegations of racism. Submissions from the National Healthcare Professionals Association, Discovery, GEMS and Medscheme, and medical aid members are expected. eNCA’s Janke Tolmay is at that inquiry.